.TH DASALL 1 "2026-05-08" "DASALL" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dasall \- installed DASALL command-line client
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dasall
.I command
[options]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dasall
is the installed command name for the DASALL CLI shipped by the Debian and
Ubuntu packages. The source-tree target name
.B dasall-cli
is not part of the package-facing operator surface.

The v1 local control-plane operator path is root/sudo-only. Use
.B sudo dasall
for local daemon operations.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B help
Show command usage.
.TP
.B version
Print CLI version and schema support information.
.TP
.B ping
Query daemon reachability.
.TP
.B readiness
Query daemon readiness summary.
.TP
.BI "run " JSON_PAYLOAD
Submit a unary request payload.
.TP
.BI "status " RECEIPT_REF " " OWNERSHIP_TOKEN " [" ACTOR_REF "]"
Query the status of an async receipt.
.TP
.BI "cancel " RECEIPT_REF " " OWNERSHIP_TOKEN " [" ACTOR_REF "]"
Cancel an async receipt.
.SH PACKAGE-MODE DEPLOYMENT
For package-mode deployment, the canonical operator workflow name is:

.B sudo dasall config

The canonical files remain:
.TP
.I /etc/default/dasall-daemon
Profile selection only.
.TP
.I /etc/dasall/daemon.json
Daemon override file. Only
.B daemon.*
keys are supported.

Validate a deployment configuration with:

.B . /etc/default/dasall-daemon && /usr/sbin/dasall-daemon --validate-only --profile-id="${DASALL_DAEMON_PROFILE_ID}" --config-file /etc/dasall/daemon.json
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/bin/dasall
Installed CLI command.
.TP
.I /usr/sbin/dasall-daemon
Installed daemon binary.
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/dasall-daemon/README.Debian
Package deployment notes.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dasall-daemon (8)